<item>
            <title>[LU-8291] configure: error: can&apos;t compile with OpenIB gen2 headers</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-8291</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Hi,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I have a RH6.8 server (with kernel 2.6.32-642.1.1.el6.x86_64) and Mellanox OFED 3.3.1.0.0.0 (the only one supported for RH6.8 as od today).&lt;br/&gt;
When I try to build the lustre client I get the following:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;root@varuna1 ~&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;# rpmbuild --rebuild --define &apos;configure_args --with-o2ib=/usr/src/ofa_kernel/default --disable-server --enable-client&apos; --without servers lustre-client-2.8.0-2.6.32_573.12.1.el6.x86_64.src.rpm&lt;br/&gt;
...&lt;br/&gt;
checking if Linux kernel has tunable backoff TCP support... no&lt;br/&gt;
checking whether to use Compat RDMA... yes&lt;br/&gt;
checking whether to use any OFED backport headers... no&lt;br/&gt;
checking whether to enable OpenIB gen2 support... no&lt;br/&gt;
configure: error: can&apos;t compile with OpenIB gen2 headers under /usr/src/ofa_kernel/default&lt;br/&gt;
error: Bad exit status from /var/tmp/rpm-tmp.jpa8cA (%build)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Do you have any hint for this issue?&lt;br/&gt;
Thanks in advance,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Giuseppe&lt;/p&gt;</description>
